item.title: Professional KPI dashboards required for industry clients - Upwork
item.description:
We are looking for a professional with experience in data visualization and dashboard creation to create two KPI dashboards for industry clients - two dashboards with the same KPIs and data visualization and slightly different branding and data inputs.

The data has already been collected, cleaned and organized according to client expectations in five strategic sections (each a new report page/slide).  We require a specialist in data visualisation to effectively design and construct two dashboards, using the same strcuture with slightly different branding each.  These need to reflect our brand and encapsulate an aesthetic similar to a polished PowerPoint presentation used at top management consulting levels.

Required skills: Mastery of PowerBI and PowerPoint.  The ability to create seamless, professional, visually appealing aesthetics in PowerBI are essential.

The dashboards need to be interactive, and be able to be shared with interactive capabilities with clients that may not have access to PowerBI premium.

Task Details and Expected Output:
1.  Effective data visualisation with given KPIs, strategic themes and data
2.  Expert in PowerBI and/or PowerBI into PowerPoint
3.  Quality design using given colour schemes and themes, to embody a professional and sophisticated look reminiscent of high-quality PowerPoint presentations, while being interactive and dynamic
4.  Create a skeleton framework with the dashboard replicable for two clients, and which can be updated each year with new data
5.  Duplicate the skeleton dashboard to provide a professional, visually appealing dashboard for two industry clients (same KPIs, slightly different data, colour scheme and branding)

Timeline:  The project start date is scheduled for the 23/05/2024.
We anticipate this task within 10 days from the start date, with two progress milestones - one halfway, and one 1/2 days before completing the task.

The chosen candidate must be open to one review prior to commencement to ensure alignment, and one prior to completion with suggested revisions and input given to achieve the desired final product.

Data Management and Privacy: Prior to initiating any project tasks, you will be required to sign a confidentiality agreement with our company.



Budget: $300
Posted On: May 16, 2024 09:28 UTC
Category: Data Visualization
Skills:Dashboard, Data Visualization, Microsoft Power BI, Microsoft Excel, Data Analysis
Skills: Dashboard, Data Visualization, Microsoft Power BI, Microsoft Excel, Data Analysis
Country: South Africa

item.title: Data Analytics Specialist - Upwork
item.description:
We are seeking an experienced Analytics Specialist to join our software company. In this role, you will play a critical role in collecting, analyzing, and visualizing essential data and Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) to drive data-informed decision-making across the organization.

The quick look:

- Part time (15-20 hours/week) role with opportunity to transition to more hours or even full time.
- Small, growing startup (15 employees)
- You will be the only analytics / data member on the team
- Focus on visualization and weekly/monthly reporting
- Flexible hours and scheduled, must be available at least 2 hours/day within normal EST working hours

Responsibilities:

1. **Data Collection:** Design and implement data collection processes to gather relevant data from various sources

2. **Data Analysis:** Utilize advanced analytical techniques to analyze large datasets and identify trends, patterns, and insights that can inform strategic business decisions.

3. **KPI Development:** Work closely with stakeholders to define key metrics and KPIs that align with business objectives and measure the success of various initiatives.

4. **Visualization:** Develop visually compelling dashboards and reports using data visualization tools such as Tableau, Power BI, or Google Data Studio to effectively communicate insights and trends to stakeholders at all levels of the organization.

5. **Continuous Improvement:** Continuously monitor data quality and accuracy, and proactively identify opportunities to enhance data collection processes and analytical methodologies.

6. **Cross-Functional Collaboration:** Collaborate with cross-functional teams including product management, marketing, sales, and finance to provide actionable insights and support data-driven decision-making.

Requirements:

1. Proven experience in data analytics, including data collection, analysis, and visualization.

3. Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with the ability to translate complex data into actionable insights.

4. Experience with data visualization tools such as Tableau, Power BI, or Google Data Studio.

5. Excellent communication and interpersonal skills with the ability to effectively collaborate with cross-functional teams.

6. Strong attention to detail and ability to manage multiple priorities in a fast-paced environment.

Join us and be part of a team that leverages data to drive innovation and deliver exceptional results!

Hourly Range: $15.00-$20.00

Category: Data Analytics
Skills:Dashboard, Data Analysis, Analytics, Data Visualization, Data Science
Skills: Dashboard, Data Analysis, Analytics, Data Visualization, Data Science

item.title: Expert Power Bi Developer for Dashboard (3 pages and single Excel data source) - Upwork
item.description:
I am looking for a seasoned expert in PowerBi in order to implement a dashboard and your profile looks very interesting to me. I provide you below with a broad generic description of the project.  If interested,  please feel free to reach me for more detailed questions.

Project Overview:
Develop a dashboard for an internal tool within a diverse organizational context. The dashboard will display monthly performance across several distinct organizational areas. It will provide aggregated visualizations to track performance against fixed set targets using various charts (barplot, donut, timeline), summary tables, maps, and interactive elements such data drills and slicers. The primary audience will be project managers.  Visualizations might include aggregated numerical tables, some maps and other easy to interpret visualizations (timelines, barplots and donut charts) with drill menus and a timeline slicer by months (with cumulative figures functionality). The audience is mostly project managers so no need for very complicated visuals. The dashboard will very likely include 3 separate sheets

Technical Requirements:

- The data source will be a unique Excel workbook with several sheets for each organizational unit
- You will not need to deal with the Excel itself, as it is already prepared to collect the data in a clean way using many internal validations and dropdowns to ensure that the data feeded to PowerBi is as clean as possible
- Initial query connections and data wrangling will be done to provide a combined dataset for easy filtering, as a starting point.
- The PowerBi .pbix and Excel data source file will be hosted on the same SharePoint folder for seamless connection
- Each of the organizational units excel sheets have identical column names across areas, with variations in some specific indicator categories depending on the organizational unit.
- Data will usually be aggregated at subnational level1 and second subnational level2. Entities have standardized names to facilitate PowerBI mapping capabilities. Map visualizations will be either bubble maps or choropleth.
- Draft wireframes with suggested visuals and tables will be provided to guide the development process
- Guidance and feedback will be provided through the phases to facilitate the specialist work.
- More details on the project will be provided to preselected candidates in order to better frame the scope

I look forward to collaborating with a skilled specialist to create the basis for an effective and user-friendly dashboard within the suggested timeframe and budget.

Budget: $2,000

Category: Data Visualization
Skills:Dashboard, Microsoft Power BI, Data Visualization, Business Intelligence, Data Modeling
Skills: Dashboard, Microsoft Power BI, Data Visualization, Business Intelligence, Data Modeling

item.description:
Hi
Please apply if you match the following job requirements and if you are available immediately-

Mandatory Skills:

·         Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, or a related field.
·         5+ years of experience in BI development, data warehousing, ETL, SSIS, Oracle and analytics
·         Proficiency in SQL programming and database technologies such as SQL Server, Oracle, or MySQL.
·         Hands-on experience with ETL tools and processes, such as SSIS, Informatica, or Talend.
·         Expertise in data modeling techniques and dimensional modeling principles.
·         Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to translate complex business requirements into technical solutions.

BI Solution Development: Design, develop, and implement scalable BI solutions to extract, transform, and load data from various sources into data warehouses or data marts.
Data Modeling: Develop and maintain logical and physical data models to support business requirements and optimize query performance.
ETL Processes: Design, develop, and optimize Extract, Transform, Load (ETL) processes to ensure data integrity, accuracy, and timeliness.
Data Visualization: Create interactive and intuitive dashboards, reports, and data visualizations using BI tools such as Power BI, Tableau, or QlikView.



Preferred Qualifications:

·         Master’s degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, or a related field.
·         Certifications in BI technologies (e.g., Microsoft Certified: Data Analyst Associate, Tableau Desktop Certified Associate).
·         Experience with cloud-based BI platforms such as Azure BI, AWS Redshift, or Google Big Query.

item.description:
We are seeking a skilled professional to assist us with setting up permissions and authentication in Snowflake and integrating Snowflake with Tableau. The goal is to allow users to connect to Snowflake from Tableau without having to manually log in to Snowflake within the Tableau interface.
